    "2017) are the de-facto paradigm for learning on graphs.",
    "Their key inductive bias is invariance to node relabelings (permutations), a symmetry constraint representing a core tenet of Geometric Deep Learning (Bronstein et al. 2021).",
    "This ensures models depend only on the isomorphism class of a graph rather than arbitrary encodings, supporting generalization and sample efficiency (Tahmasebi and Jegelka 2023).",
    "However, this bias limits expressivity for GNNs of tractable complexity (Morris et al. 2019; Chen et al.",
    "2020).LLMs on graphs and graph reasoning."
